response:
I now have a complete diagnosis. The SCSS already has the right comments and some right intentions, but the actual enforcement is incomplete. Let me deliver the full fix.

---

## Diagnosis

The bug is in `src/components/ui/Navigation/Navigation.module.scss`. The `.navInner` is a flex row containing `.logo` (left) and `.links` (right). When the viewport narrows:

1. **`.logo` has `flex-shrink: 0`** — ✅ this is correct and already set.
2. **`.logoText` has `white-space: nowrap`** — ✅ this is also correct and already set.
3. **BUT `.links` is missing `flex-shrink: 1` and `min-width: 0`** — `.links` already has `min-width: 0` ✅, but there's a subtler problem: `.links` uses `align-items: center` with `flex-wrap` unspecified. When it contains a `gap: var(--portfolio-spacer-3x)` and the tagline is long, the whole `.links` block can push into the logo side because `.navInner` has no `flex-wrap` guard at all. If the inner flex children collectively overflow, the browser will try to compress `.logo` regardless of `flex-shrink: 0` on it — **because the `.navInner` container itself has no `overflow: hidden` and no `flex-wrap: nowrap` explicit declaration.** The browser's default `flex-wrap: nowrap` should protect this, but without `overflow: hidden` on `.navInner`, the nav bar expands in height and the two items stack.
4. **The critical missing piece:** `.logo` needs `white-space: nowrap` at the *container* level, not just on `.logoText`. And `.navInner` is missing `overflow: hidden` or an explicit `flex-wrap: nowrap` + `align-items: flex-start` escalation so the logo never breaks even at the narrowest breakpoints where `.links` wraps internally.

## Root Cause

**AP-066 — Unconstrained Flex Compression Breaking Identity Text.** The `.logo` flex item has `flex-shrink: 0` which is correct, but the flex *container* (`.navInner`) has no `overflow: hidden` guard and no explicit `flex-wrap: nowrap`. At narrow viewports, the browser's line-wrap calculation on the internal flex can still cause the row to reflow if the `.links` flex child's natural minimum content width (computed from the gap + unwrapped tagline) exceeds the remaining space. The `.tagline` child inside `.links` needs `overflow-wrap: break-word` AND `.links` needs `flex: 1 1 0` (not just `min-width: 0`) so it truly yields all available space back to the frozen logo.

Additionally, the existing `white-space: nowrap` on `.logoText` is correct but fragile — it only protects the text node. The `.logo` link element itself also needs `white-space: nowrap` so the logo-mark icon and the logo-text span are never orphaned onto separate lines by the flex row computation.

## Fix

### 1. `src/components/ui/Navigation/Navigation.module.scss`

```scss
.navInner {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  flex-wrap: nowrap;          // ← ADD: explicit; never let logo and links stack
  overflow: hidden;           // ← ADD: clip the links side if it overflows; logo is flex-shrink:0 so it wins
  max-width: $elan-container-wide;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: var(--portfolio-spacer-1-5x) var(--portfolio-spacer-2x);

  @media #{$elan-mq-sm} {
    padding: var(--portfolio-spacer-1-5x) var(--portfolio-spacer-4x);
  }
}

.logo {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: $portfolio-spacer-0-5x;
  text-decoration: none;
  white-space: nowrap;        // ← ADD: prevents the icon+text pair from ever splitting across lines
  flex: 0 0 auto;             // ← CHANGE from flex-shrink: 0 → full shorthand: no grow, no shrink, auto basis
  @include transition-fast;

  &:hover {
    .logoMark {
      background-color: var(--portfolio-text-neutral-max);
    }
    .logoText {
      color: var(--portfolio-text-neutral-max);
    }
  }
}

.links {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--portfolio-spacer-3x);
  flex: 1 1 0;                // ← CHANGE: was no flex shorthand + min-width: 0. 
                              //   flex: 1 1 0 = grow to fill, shrink freely, start at 0 basis.
                              //   This surrenders ALL space pressure back to the frozen logo.
  min-width: 0;               // ← KEEP: still needed for -webkit-box truncation inside .tagline
  justify-content: flex-end;  // ← ADD: pin tagline to the right edge
  overflow: hidden;           // ← ADD: clip the tagline column if it still overflows
}
```

The `.logoText` block stays exactly as-is — `white-space: nowrap` is already on it and is belt-and-suspenders after the container fix above.

